    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/external-review-of-government-planning-practice-guidance"/>
    <title>External review of government planning practice guidance</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>Conclusions and recommendations of the review of planning guidance led by Lord Taylor of Goss Moor.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;On &lt;a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/planning-practice-guidance-should-be-simpler"&gt;21 December 2012&lt;/a&gt; the government welcomed the report of the review of planning practice guidance led by Lord Taylor of Goss Moor, and announced a &lt;a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/review-of-planning-practice-guidance"&gt;short consultation&lt;/a&gt; on the review group’s recommendations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The review group’s report makes recommendations as to the scope and form of practice guidance that should be provided in future by government to support effective planning; what new or updated practice guidance should be published, with clear priorities; and what guidance should be cancelled.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
